15/02/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Officials say a high-ranking NATO delegation will visit Croatia this week. 
Led by the NATO secretary general's deputy assistant, Robert Simmons, the group will meet with senior officials to discuss implementation of the 2003-2004 annual national programme, viewed as a yardstick measuring progress under the Membership Action Plan. 
Future steps would also be outlined.
In other news, tourism officials expect to see a spike in the number of Germans visiting Croatia. 
An estimated 3 per cent more are expected to visit this year than last, according to Niko Bulic, director of the Croatian National Tourist Board. 
(HINA - 14/02/04; HINA - 13/02/04)
